text:
A general view north from the Williamsburg Bridge at a point between Kent Ave. (left) and Wythe Street (right). South 5th Street is in the foreground (not shown). The Austin Nichols and Company warehouse seen in the background is on the N.W. corner of Kent Ave. and North 3rd Street.

June 25, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
title: General View - Brooklyn - Williamsburg Bridge - betw. Kent Avenue - Wythe Street.
